👉 Commit AFTER processing = At least once guarantee

🎯 Interview Answer
❓ “Why manual commit?”

✅ Prevent data loss + ensure reliability

🟡 4. FAILURE SCENARIOS (INTERVIEW CRITICAL)
🔥 Scenario 1: Crash BEFORE commit
Process → Crash → Restart

👉 Kafka will reprocess message ✅

👉 Result:

No data loss
Possible duplicate
🔥 Scenario 2: Crash AFTER commit

👉 Message already marked processed

👉 Result:

No reprocessing
Safe
🎯 Interview Answer
❓ “What happens if consumer crashes?”

✅ Reprocess from last committed offset

🔴 5. IDEMPOTENCY (MUST KNOW)
🧠 Problem

Kafka = At least once

👉 Same event can come twice ❗

🔥 Solution

Use eventId

processed_events = set()

def process(event):
    if event["eventId"] in processed_events:
        return

    # process logic
    processed_events.add(event["eventId"])
🧠 Real Production

👉 Store in DB / Redis (not memory)

🎯 Interview Answer
❓ “How do you handle duplicate events?”

✅ Idempotency using unique eventId

